CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 28, 1946, pg. 9, reads: "Charmers - Ida Mae Townsend and Malcome Bailey practice for the cameraman before going before the patrons of the Bon Club's Yuletide performance at Northside Elks, Dec. 27. These young ladies are due to open [illegible] the eyes of the spectators. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Ida Mae Townsend and Malcome Bailey posed in YMCA with fleur de lis patterned wallpaper
